originalText.text: My wife and I have been going to Dina for the past 10 years and she is absolutely amazing.  Regarding the negative reviews, if you are going close to Tax day and it is a weekend, be prepared to wait.  Go in January/February or if you do not expect to owe taxes, you can always file after the deadline (There is no penalty for filing a late return if you are due a refund)...

originalText.text: Dina Rosa is an very professional and experienced tax professional. She is expert in helping you receive the best possible tax return under the law. She treats every person with respect and is interested in resolving all major tax problems you may encounter. You have to be patient because she does have a large client following. You must make an appointment in advance but it will be worth your while to contact her and see how she can help you prepare your taxes.

originalText.text: I have been a faithful client of Dina! For the last 6-7 years I have experienced a professional relationship but today I was extremely disappointed. I remember Dina when she worked out of the check cashing place on 14th street. As her popularity has increased the business courtesy has decreased. As a business owner don't have people standing on line for hours in the cold and then come late. Don't have your less than professional assistant tell me after I get there that they are closed and aren't seeing any additional clients at 9:00 am because I didn't stand outside at 6:00am to be seen. That's not professional behavior. This is the end of tax season accommodate those who put you on the tax map of success. But there is a lesson here. Find someone else. Don't allow those that you pay to dictate how you get treated. Yes I'm pissed!!!
